---
NavigateActions is tied to a rowset; and that object may be shared. Maybe better
situation, have a thin object, e.g. Navigation, that references, and delegates
to, a NavigateActions. Then Navigation is the model that is usually used, and it
can fire events (or send a message over the bus) when its rowset changes. As is
common, multiple components can use the same Navigation. NavigateActions is
still there pretty much as is, but hidden inside a Navigation. An example of
where this is wanted; an SSDataNavigator has a Navigation model, if the rowset
in the Navigation changes, the SSDataNavigator detects this event and adjusts
accordingly.

